  1. Â¿QuiÃ©n es el segundo âmejorâ empleado que mÃ¡s Ã³rdenes ha generado? (nombre, apellido, tÃ­tulo, cuÃ¡ndo entrÃ³ a la compaÃ±Ã­a, nÃºmero de Ã³rdenes generadas, nÃºmero de Ã³rdenes generadas por el mejor empleado (nÃºmero 1))
%spark.sql

select a.employeeid, concat(e.lastname ," ",  e.firstname) as nombre, e.title, e.hiredate, a.total, lead(a.total,1) over (order by a.total) as primero 
from ( 
  select o.employeeid, count(*) as total 
  from orders o 
  group by o.employeeid
) a 
join employees e
on e.employeeid = a.employeeid
order by primero desc limit 1

CÃ³digo E_1b.sql Resultado resultado


c. Â¿CuÃ¡l es el delta de tiempo mÃ¡s grande entre una orden y otra?

%spark.sql

select orderid, from_utc_timestamp(date_format(orderdate,'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS'),'UTC') as orderdate , 
datediff(orderdate, lag(orderdate) over (order by orderid)) as diferencia
from orders 
order by diferencia desc
limit 1

Ejercicio 2. Con los archivos de vuelos, aeropuertos y aerolÃ­neas que estÃ¡n en el dropbox

  1. Â¿QuÃ© aerolÃ­neas (nombres) llegan al aeropuerto âHonolulu International Airportâ?
%spark.sql

select distinct(f.airline) as airline, a.airline from flights f 
join airlines a 
on a.iata_code = f.airline
where destination_airport = 'HNL'

CÃ³digo E_2a.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿En quÃ© horario (hora del dÃ­a, no importan los minutos) hay salidas del aeropuerto de San Francisco (âSFOâ) a âHonolulu International Airportâ?
%spark.sql

select distinct substring(lpad(scheduled_departure,4,"0"),1,2) as hora 
from flights f where f.destination_airport ='HNL' and f.origin_airport ='SFO'

CÃ³digo E_2b.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿QuÃ© dÃ­a de la semana y en quÃ© aerolÃ­nea nos conviene viajar a âHonolulu International Airportâ para tener el menor retraso posible?
%spark.sql

select f.day_of_week, f.airline, a.airline, min(cast (f.departure_delay as int))  as minimo
 from flights f 
 join airlines a 
 on a.iata_code = f.airline 
where f.destination_airport ='HNL' 
group by f.day_of_week, f.airline, a.airline
order by minimo asc limit 1

CÃ³digo E_2c.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿CuÃ¡l es el aeropuerto con mayor trÃ¡fico de entrada?
%spark.sql

select  f.destination_airport, a.airport, count(f.destination_airport) as total_llegadas
 from flights f 
 join airports a 
 on a.iata_code = f.destination_airport 
 group by f.destination_airport, a.airport
 order by total_llegadas desc limit 1

CÃ³digo E_2d.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿CuÃ¡l es la aerolÃ­nea con mayor retraso de salida por dÃ­a de la semana?
%spark.sql

select f.airline, a.airline, f.day_of_week , cast(f.departure_delay as int) as departure_delay from flights f 
    join (
    select day_of_week, max(cast(departure_delay as int) ) as maximo from flights group by day_of_week
    ) ff 
    on  f.departure_delay = ff.maximo
    join airlines a 
    on f.airline = a.iata_code
    order by f.day_of_week

CÃ³digo E_2e.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿CuÃ¡l es la tercer aerolÃ­nea con menor retraso de salida los lunes (day of week = 2)?
%spark.sql

select * from (
select  f.airline, a.airline, min(cast(f.departure_delay as int)) as menor
 from flights f 
 join airlines a 
 on a.iata_code = f.airline 
 where day_of_week = 2
 group by f.airline, a.airline
 order by menor asc limit 3) aerolineas 
 order by aerolineas.menor desc
 limit 1

CÃ³digo E_2f.sql Resultado resultado


  1. Â¿CuÃ¡l es el aeropuerto origen que llega a la mayor cantidad de aeropuertos destino diferentes?
%spark.sql

select a.airport, count(distinct f.destination_airport) as total_destinos
 from flights f 
 join airports a 
 on a.iata_code = f.origin_airport 
 group by a.airport
 order by total_destinos desc limit 1
